    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-31T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="1005"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1005">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.W./10–3145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-31T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 31, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 1—3:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3363. As regards so-called revision of armistice terms (see Department’s 1963,
                    October 30, 9 p.m.). I inquire if Department proposes to go ahead with
                    publication of long armistice terms without obtaining a definite request
                    therefor from Italian Government, (see my 3054, October 11)<note n="95"
                        xml:id="d1005fn1">Not printed.</note> or at least submitting to Government
                    in advance the prepared text of statement of terms with “other pertinent papers
                    and agreed commentary”. As the Department is aware, I recommend obtaining a
                    definite request in this regard from Italian Government. Furthermore, I hope the
                    Department will insist on allowing Italian Government to participate in an
                    eventual publication. (See my 55, July 24, 1944).<note n="95" xml:id="d1005fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note> I should also like to know if Department has rejected
                    suggestion that publication long armistice terms be postponed until it may be
                    possible to include the terms of a document in the form of a <hi rend="italic"
                        >modus vivendi</hi> in substitution of armistice terms. (See my 1448, May
                        29).<note n="95" xml:id="d1005fn3">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated Am PolAd 930, sent Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
